<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: The PPU Attribute Table concept]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5040&amp;p=45428#p45428"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">dreampeppers99 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />When I mean "in line or like the drawing" I was refering to the original docs that I've read, they say the Name Table is 32x30, with this assumption the model 1 seems to be impossible! (will leak two line) Am I rigth?<br /></div><br />"Model 1" is the correct one. It is true that 64 attribute bytes can define the palettes used by 32x32 tiles, while the name tables only has 32x30, but don't let that confuse you. Half of the bits of the last 8 bytes in the attribute table are simply not used.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Thu Apr 09, 2009 4:31 pm</p><hr />
